div.p: IDT size: 256 entries 8 bytes = 2048 bytes IDTR: limit = 2047, base = (uint32_t)idt

g.text: Kernel Exception Gate (e.g., #PF handler, IRQ0 timer)

div.p: P Present Must = 1 for valid gate. CPU ignores entries with P=0.
DPL Descriptor Privilege Level DPL=0 only ring 0 can int n DPL=3 ring 3 can int n (syscalls) Hardware IRQs bypass DPL check.
TYPE Gate Type (4 bits) 1110 = 32-bit Interrupt Gate 1111 = 32-bit Trap Gate Bit 4 is always 0 (shown separately).
Clears EFLAGS.IF on entry interrupts disabled until handler calls sti or iretd. Use for: all hardware IRQs, all CPU exceptions.
Preserves EFLAGS.IF kernel remains interruptible during handler. Use for: INT 0x80 system call gate.
0x8E = 1000_1110 P=1, DPL=00, type=1110 (interrupt) handler = 0x10C0CDAB | selector = 0x0008 (kernel code)
0xEF = 1110_1111 P=1, DPL=11 (user!), type=1111 (trap) handler = 0x10C03412 | selector = 0x0008 (kernel code)
